ObAgent: uncertain.

Reason: latencies rose across services while disk I/O fell and processed row_count dropped — this could be network-induced slowdowns (packet loss/retransmits or socket errors) or a downstream slowdown reducing IOPS, not a clear CPU/memory/disk saturation signal. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric("net.tcp.retransmits") and whether_is_abnormal_metric("net.packet_loss") (for packet loss/network issues);
- whether_is_abnormal_metric("application.socket_errors" or "tcp.connect_errors") (for socket errors);
- whether_is_abnormal_metric("cpu.usage") and whether_is_abnormal_metric("disk.await" or "disk.latency") (to rule out CPU or disk contention).
JudgeAgent: No - The agents produced hypotheses (e.g., network latency) but did not pin a single component + one closed-set anomaly + a concrete telemetry reason. Multiple services (emailservice, currencyservice, recommendationservice, and root->service trace row_count drops) show anomalies and there is no confirming network metric (e.g., net.tcp.retransmits, NIC errors) or single service KPI/log that uniquely identifies one root cause.

